## Priority 1 Issues

### 0. Weather data never loads when berry data comes from localStorage cache
**File:** `js/app.js:18–26,173–193`

**Root cause:** When cached berry data exists (the common path on repeat visits), `onDataLoaded()` fires *before* Supabase is initialized:

```
Line 18: DataStore.loadCache() → true
Line 19: this.onDataLoaded()  ← fires immediately
Line 21: DataStore.initSupabase().then(...)  ← runs LATER in background
```

Inside `onDataLoaded()` (line 181), `WeatherStore.load()` runs but immediately returns `false` because `DataStore.supabase` is `null`. The background Supabase init (line 21–26) never re-triggers `WeatherStore.load()`, so `WeatherStore.data` stays empty for the entire session.

When the user navigates to Vendimias, `Charts.createWeatherTimeSeries()` calls `WeatherStore.getRange()` on an empty dataset → returns `[]` → renders "Sin datos de temperatura disponibles".

**Fix:** After Supabase initializes in the cache path, trigger weather loading. In `app.js` around line 21–26:

```js
DataStore.initSupabase().then(() => {
  DataStore.loadFromSupabase().then(loaded => {
    if (loaded && this.initialized) this.refresh();
    this._updateDbStatus();
  }).catch(err => console.error('Supabase load failed:', err));

  // Weather: load from Supabase meteorology table now that connection is ready
  WeatherStore.load().then(hasCache => {
    const vintages = WeatherStore.getVintagesFromData();
    if (!vintages.length) return;
    WeatherStore.sync(vintages).then(() => {
      if (this.currentView === 'vintage') this.refresh();
    });
    if (hasCache && this.currentView === 'vintage') this.refresh();
  });
}).catch(err => console.error('Supabase init failed:', err));
```

This ensures weather loads regardless of whether berry data came from cache or Supabase.

